rComments: Used another profs notes because he didn't have any. Didn't care if people didn't understand a concept, it's "on them" to figure it out. Assigned insane amounts of homework.

Honestly Ali is the absolute worst Professor I have ever had. He is rude, blunt, and shows no interest or care towards his students or their success. His lectures are useless and he doesn't convey the material well at all. Only reason I did well is from teaching myself using the textbook. STAY AWAY

Prof Karimnezhad was utterly horrible. His way of "teaching" was just to sloppily read off another professors lecture notes to the class without really conveying the actual concepts to us. I stopped going to class and just did the practice problems from the textbook before midterms. If I hadn't taken calc in high school I probably would've failed.

AVOID!! He's nice but sucks at teaching. Awful at explain concepts and answering questions. I had to do prep101 in order to learn the concepts. Be prepared to teach yourself all the course material if you have him :/

I taught the entirety of the content of this class to myself using the textbook. Ali was useless as a professor. He was never available outside of class during the whole exam period. Luckily, the assignments, midterm, and exam content closely reflects what's in the textbook, which is the only reason I was able to get an okay mark.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: This professor is very poor. He has no idea how to teach, and is rude.

Ali seems nice; however, he cannot teach. He cannot clearly explain the topics and his slides aren't great. Definitely use the textbook to teach yourself instead. The material is not hard to teach yourself but that obviously does not work for everyone. The other section of this class had a much higher average and was better prepared for the final.

He struggles to convey his messages effectively to the class. The lectures consisted of him writing on the blackboards in a very, very unorganized manner. He'd sometimes read off of the projector as well when he was able to get it working. Avoid this professor at all costs, unless you're able to learn the subject matter on your own.

Doesn't cover examples in class. You have to learn everything on your own. He always talked about how busy he was and how he didn't have any time. In fact, he cancelled the last class before the exam because he was "unavailable" & told us he wouldn't be answering emails so find help elsewhere. Would not recommend, take the class with another prof

The material in this class isn't too hard, but Ali overcomplicates everything in class. He doesn't complete any examples, and his power points also don't contain many examples. Just follow the textbook.

Genuinely embarrassing that the university hired him. He skips numerous slides, doesn't follow them in order (ex: slide 20 then slide 10 without reason), can't elaborate or clarify the few examples he has, fails to teach the application of the theory and is horrible at reading his class. I got an A+ on the first midterm using another prof's notes.

Terrible prof. Uses another prof's notes but you can tell he does not read them before hand. Does not explain what he is during doing class. Can be hard to understand at times. Midterms are not very difficult if you can manage to understand the material, which is hard with him as a prof. Don't bother going to the lectures, teach yourself at home.

He's not a very organized prof. Often switches between using another teachers notes on the projector or writing incredibly small on the chalkboard. Doesn't really explain anything during class either. You're better off just skipping class as the other professors notes he uses are pretty good. Midterms were pretty easy however.
Worst teacher I've had in uni thus far. Doesn't even understand what he is teaching and cannot answer questions properly. Expects students to get an A from grade F teaching. Horrible, do not do it!

Don't even go to the lectures/dgds as you will just waste your time. I got a D on my first midterm, stopped going to the lectures and watched youtube videos. On the 2nd midterm, I got an A while the class average was a D+. He's not great at explaining concepts, doesn't use a microphone, his handwriting is smalland he makes mistakes somewhat often.

Not a great teacher, occasionally skips over lectures, all his material is made by other professors, and he isn't good at explaining the concepts. 90% of the time in his lectures you will be trying to understand his notes and ignoring him

Does not know how to teach. Will skip over important examples and assume you know how to do it. Lecture notes are constantly updated because they are littered with so many errors. Learn from your textbook
Terrible prof. Thought i was good at math but this guy cant teach. Uses other profs notes. All lectures all posted on BS.

He's a solid meh, should not be really teaching though. Biostats is pretty heavily structured and the profs don't have any freedom with regards to how they teach it. What freedom he has, he does not use. Textbook (written by a prof at UO) is pretty bad and a lot of the solutions in the back are incorrect (verified with external solutions sets).

Has only 1 hour of office hours a week, making him impossible to contact. Has no idea how to properly explain concepts and thinks repeating what he said slower is the answer. Did not use his own lecture notes, rather he used notes from another professor. Only take his class if you already know the concepts.
